Job description
**Director, CCO Regional Coverage Business Strategy, HSBC Securities (USA) Inc., New York, NY:**

Responsible to ensure the support of the successful day to day running of the business. Global responsibilities in addition to supporting their regional heads’ business development, strategic execution, and business management needs and executing our centrally driven programs in-region. Play a key role across several of the Chief Commercial Office (CCO) pillars, including reporting and tracking of business performance, analytics and management information. Support the Head of GB Regional Coverage, Americas and the respective coverage business heads. Supporting GB Regional Coverage by working with the Head of Strategy & Execution to provide timely and insightful business performance data that supports strategy execution. Monitoring and report relevant developments relating to market dynamics, peers, benchmarks to help guide and further refine strategic execution, providing ongoing feedback to the global/regional strategy team. Preparing monthly risk and business performance escalation for Global Banking and regional cross line of business governance forums ensuring consistent messaging. Ensuring effective and globally consistent application of business selection processes, pipeline line management and cross business collaborations (e.g. CAC). Focusing on outcomes that promote a positive client experience, with a particular focus on ease-of-doing-business. Strategic business development and coordination within the Regional Coverage teams, and related functions (Finance, Regulatory Compliance, Financial Crime, HR, Wholesale Risk, etc.) for Global Banking. Proactively engaging with stakeholders across the Banking, WCOO, and Global Functions community in the US, Canada, and Latin America to ensure strong communication and escalation of risk and business issues. Identifying opportunities to increase effectiveness and provide constructive challenge to existing practices. Ensuring embedded behaviors to drive Banking's success under the GB Culture Uplift Framework. Promoting a positive people agenda across Regional Coverage, one that results in a culture and behaviors that embody HSBC’s purpose, values and conduct pillars. Assisting with any other requested projects or initiatives within the CCO organization. Supporting engagement with regulators on behalf of Regional Coverage, in full partnership with Regulatory Compliance and relevant Global Banking & Group colleagues. Responsible for identifying and implementing further areas of impactful change.



#LI-DNIFull time employment, Monday – Friday, 40 hours per week, Pay range: $205,101 - $210,000 per year.


Requirements
Must have a Bachelor’s degree or foreign equivalent in Economics, Business Administration, Finance, Mathematics, or a closely related field and at least 8 years of related work experience. Employer will accept a 3- or 4-year bachelor’s degree.





Must have 5 years of experience in:


* Corporate Banking industry;


* Financial industry risk management;


* Global Banking business;


* Investment Banking products: Debt Capital Markets, Leverage Finance Acquisition, Equity Capital Market, M&A, Payments, Trade Finance, Credit and Lending, Structured Finance and Data analytics;


* Compliance;


* Human Resources: Workforce planning, Organizational design, Recruitment, Training and Performance and Rewards;


* Resource Management;


* Operating Plan and forecasting; and


* Event Planning.


Employer will accept any suitable combination of education, training or experience.

**If you would like to apply to this position, please click the 'Apply' button.**


***In compliance with applicable laws, HSBC is committed to employing only those who are authorized to work in the US. Applicants must be legally authorized to work in the U.S. as HSBC will not engage in immigration sponsorship for this position. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, disability, or status as a protected veteran.***  

***At HSBC, our overall goal is to provide a competitive Total Reward Package, with an appropriate mix of fixed pay, and variable pay, as part of an employee’s overall total compensation and benefits. Variable pay generally takes the form of discretionary, annual awards (sometimes referred to as a “bonus”). Additionally, HSBC offers a competitive benefits package including a robust Wellness Hub, in a welcoming, diverse, and inclusive work environment. You will have access to tailored professional development opportunities to ensure you have the right skills for today and tomorrow. You will be empowered to drive HSBC’s engagement with the communities we serve through an industry-leading volunteerism policy, a generous matching gift program, and a comprehensive program of immersive Sustainability and Climate Change Initiatives. You’ll want to join our Employee Resource Groups as they play a central part in life at HSBC, including the development of our employees and networking inside and outside of HSBC. We value difference. We succeed together. We take responsibility. We get it done. And we want you to help us build the bank of the future!***
